    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Order Setup\n Managing the Billing Day of Month\n Legal Entities\n Billing Accounts\n Recurring Billing for Subscription Products\n Grouping Order Products into Invoices\n Billing Frequency\n Advance and Arrears Billing\n Payment Terms\n Billing Dates\n Proration in CPQ Order Products\n Set Up Standalone Orders\n Enable Standalone Orders\n Creation and Activation Guidelines for Standalone Orders\n Revenue Recognition for Standalone Orders\n Limitations for Standalone Orders\n Standalone Order Product Pricing\n Required Configurations for Types of Standalone Order Products\n Overriding Billing Dates\n Order Creation and Activation\n Billing Status Fields\n Proration with Invoices\n Billing and Invoice Cancellation\n Aligning Proration Between CPQ and Billing\n Align CPQ and Billing Cancellation Based on Billing Periods\n Troubleshooting Proration Issues\n CPQ Billing Field Mapping\n Billing Order Fields\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nSet Up Standalone Orders\n\nManage your orders and order products in Salesforce and Salesforce Billing without first creating a CPQ quote. We call this type of order a standalone order. They’re useful if you manage your quotes and opportunities in an external platform but plan to use Salesforce Billing for order management and billing.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Salesforce Billing Winter ’21 and later\n\nOur standalone orders documentation contains required fields and setup instructions unique to standalone orders and order products. For concepts shared between standard orders and standalone orders, we provide links to the original CPQ and Billing topics.\n\nYou still need the Salesforce CPQ package installed to create standalone orders and order products. While you won’t use any Salesforce CPQ features or objects, Salesforce Billing runs internal validations against the CPQ package for several features and workflows.\n\nIMPORTANT Standalone order products and order products made in Salesforce CPQ can't be on the same order.\nEnable Standalone Orders\nOrders and order products created in Salesforce CPQ have several field values inherited from parent products and quote lines. When you create an order without CPQ, you must provide these values on your own or through API. Enable a set of validations that confirm that your standalone orders and order products have the correct values for Salesforce Billing features.\nCreation and Activation Guidelines for Standalone Orders\nStandalone orders and order products have several unique rules for activation.\nRevenue Recognition for Standalone Orders\nStandalone orders and order products require additional configuration for revenue recognition in Salesforce Billing.\nLimitations for Standalone Orders\nOrders and order products created without CPQ have unique guidelines and validations to ensure that Salesforce Billing can manage them. Review these guidelines when you create your orders and order products.\nStandalone Order Product Pricing\nStandalone order products require you to calculate several pricing and pricing-related fields that would otherwise come from a CPQ quote.\nRequired Configurations for Types of Standalone Order Products\nStandalone orders require you to fill out all the fields that would otherwise come from a CPQ quote. We provide a collection of topics showing all the required fields and their values for standalone order products used in different types of billing features. Certain fields require a specific value, while some are required but vary based on your specific configuration.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
